# Force LF line endings on all text files across the repo. The kit's
# scratchpad cap is measured in BYTES (via `wc -c` per design §2.1), so
# CRLF line endings on a Windows checkout would silently push files past
# their declared cap (~1 extra byte per line). LF normalization keeps
# the byte budget deterministic across platforms.
#
# Scratchpad template files (`*.template`) are the most cap-sensitive
# (some sit within 2 bytes of their cap; CRLF would push them over).
# All Markdown / YAML / JS / Python text files use LF too — consistency
# matters more than per-platform native conventions for a build artifact.
#
# Binary files (PNG, etc.) are excluded from text-conversion via the
# explicit `binary` attribute as needed; no such files exist in the
# repo today.

* text=auto eol=lf
*.template text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.mjs text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf

# claude-memory-kit:gitattributes:start v0.3.3
# claude-memory-kit — added by `cmk install`. Do not edit by hand;
# `cmk install` refreshes these lines idempotently. Remove via
# `cmk uninstall`.
#
# Force LF on the COMMITTED memory files. The kit's frontmatter parser uses
# a strict-LF boundary and split('\n') readers; default Windows git
# (autocrlf=true) rewrites line endings at clone, which made every fact
# invisible to search on a Windows checkout (D-126). The read side now
# self-heals (tolerant CRLF reads), but pinning LF here PREVENTS the
# mangling so it never has to.
#
# Scoped to the text extensions the kit actually commits (.md + .json) under
# context/ — NOT a blanket `context/** text`, so a future committed binary
# under context/ is never force-normalized + corrupted.
context/**/*.md text eol=lf
context/**/*.json text eol=lf
# claude-memory-kit:gitattributes:end
